   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">You can add additional form fields in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Define Public Portal Form Fields</uicontrol> section in addition to the default system fields. The default system fields are as follows:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Rate This Project</uicontrol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Name</uicontrol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Email</uicontrol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Comment</uicontrol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "> Zip Code</uicontrol>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Home</uicontrol> page, click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Settings</uicontrol>, and then select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Public Portal Template</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Public Portal Settings</uicontrol> page is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">DEFINE PUBLIC PORTAL FORM FIELDS</uicontrol> section, click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Add Field</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Add Custom Field</uicontrol> dialog box is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">FORM FIELD NAME</uicontrol> field, enter the name of the field.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">INPUT CONTROL TYPE</uicontrol> drop-down field, select the appropriate input type from the drop-down list.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Add</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The field is added to the form fields list.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To update or delete a custom field, perform the following:</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Click <image href="../../Icons/Edit_Icon.png"
                            class="- topic/image "
                            placement="inline"/> to edit or update information of a custom field.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Click <image href="../../Icons/Delete_Icon.png"
                            class="- topic/image "
                            placement="inline"/> to delete a custom field.</li>
               </ul>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To display the custom field in the public portal, in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Show on Public Portal</uicontrol> column, select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Yes</uicontrol> against the appropriate field.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To make the custom field as mandatory field in the public portal, in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Is a Required Field</uicontrol> column, select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Yes</uicontrol> against the appropriate field.</cmd>
         </step>
      </steps>
